# My 90 Days DevOps Learning Plan

## Current Level

I am a QA/SDET professional with 3+ years of experience in software testing and automation. I have worked on test automation, CI jobs, defect tracking, and release support. My goal is to transition into a DevOps Engineer role by learning cloud, infrastructure, automation, and deployment practices.

## My Understanding of DevOps & Cloud

For me, DevOps is about helping development and operations teams work together to deliver software faster, more reliably, and with fewer manual tasks. It focuses on automation, monitoring, deployment, and continuous improvement.

Cloud platforms provide on-demand infrastructure and services, allowing applications to be deployed, scaled, and managed efficiently without maintaining physical servers.

## Why I Am Learning DevOps

* To expand my career beyond testing and automation.
* To understand the complete software delivery lifecycle.
* To build skills that are highly demanded in modern engineering teams.
* To become a well-rounded engineer who can contribute from development to production.

## My 90-Day Goals

1. Build strong Linux, Git, and networking fundamentals.
2. Create and deploy applications using Docker, Kubernetes, and CI/CD pipelines.
3. Deploy a production-style application on AWS and manage it confidently.

## Core DevOps Skills I Want to Build

1. Linux administration and troubleshooting.
2. CI/CD pipeline creation and automation.
3. Docker, Kubernetes, and cloud deployment skills.

## Weekly Time Commitment

* Monday to Friday: 2 hours daily
* Saturday & Sunday: 4-5 hours daily
* Total: Around 18-20 hours per week

## How I Will Stay Consistent

* Study every day, even if only for 30 minutes.
* Complete one practical task before moving to the next topic.
* Maintain notes and GitHub repositories for all hands-on work.
* Share weekly progress on LinkedIn to stay accountable.
* Focus on learning by doing instead of only watching tutorials.

## Where I Want to Reach After 90 Days

By the end of this journey, I want to confidently build CI/CD pipelines, containerize applications, deploy them on Kubernetes and AWS, troubleshoot common issues, and be ready to apply for DevOps Engineer opportunities.

I will focus on consistency, hands-on practice, and continuous improvement throughout these 90 days.
